page.title: 15 WILDLIFE ALONG THE COAST
page.content: On Thursday 4th July Form 1 girls, Mrs Bennett and Mrs Coward went to Labrador Bay and walked back to school. The minibus gave us a lift to the Bay. The walk was quite interesting, it took us through a field with cows in it, a golf course and a path which was almost covered over with bracken, stinging nettles, brambles and quite a few wild flowers. The view was lovely locking over the sea, there were boats going out - fishing boats and speed boats. We made a list of all that we saw, these included birds, trees, insects and flowers. BIRDS: Skylark, robin, thrush, black- bird, swallow sparrow and magpie. TREES: Cypress, oak, sycamore, holly, hawthorn and ash. INSECTS: Blackbeetle.
